==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Goulards extract
<hw>Gou*lard"s" ex"tract"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Named after the
introducer, Thomas <ets>Goulard</ets>, a French surgeon.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An aqueous solution of the subacetate of lead,
used as a lotion in cases of inflammation. Goulard's cerate is a cerate
containing this extract.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gour</ent>⟦br⟧
